        "body": "## Operating System:\r\nAndroid 8.1\r\n## Browser:\r\nFirefox Nightly for Android 64.0.1a\r\nFirefox for Android 62.0.2\r\n## Reduced Test Case:\r\n[Can be found here](https://curtisy1.github.io/demo/bootstrap-popover)\r\n## Expected behavior:\r\nLong pressing a button in mobile browsers such as Chrome opens the popup, which makes sense in my eyes since it's mostly common knowledge that if you long press something on mobile devices, a popup might appear.\r\nThis behavior should also happen in Firefox for mobile devices\r\n## Actual behavior:\r\nLong pressing the button does nothing\r\n## Suggested fix:\r\nI'm not sure as the only fix that I can see is listening for specific browser events such as ```touchstart```, however this would probably be a massive change so I'm not fond of it either.. would be better if this is a bug within Firefox that can be identified and temporarily worked around until a fix happens.",
