        "author_association": "NONE",
        "body": "I was a bit surprised that I did not found a hover dropdown menu in Bootstrap. \r\n\r\nMost websites that I know have a dropdown navigation that appears on hover on a desktop PC like this:\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1765602/44944713-2c278d00-addc-11e8-9b83-3a3abd65e859.png)\r\n\r\nThis is also the case for the [#1 Selling HTML Template](https://themeforest.net/item/porto-responsive-html5-template/4106987?s_rank=1) on themeforest.net that buils upon Bootstrap, or allmost all Wordpress themes, like fore example here: http://www2.cuny.edu\r\n\r\nThe only thing that I found in Bootstrap were [dropdowns for tabs or pills on click](https://getbootstrap.com/docs/4.0/components/navs/#using-dropdowns) (not on hover).\r\n\r\nI wonder, is this on purpose? Is there a reason Bootstrap doesn't want to support hover-navigation's that have been around for years all over the web?\r\n\r\n",
