        "closed_at": null,
        "author_association": "NONE",
        "body": "It would be nice to have the copyright notice in the _functions.scss file.\r\n\r\nWhen using the customizing Sass option for Bootstrap ([importing ](https://getbootstrap.com/docs/4.1/getting-started/theming/#importing)just the needed parts), the copyright notice isnâ€™t automatically added to the resulting css file. The copyright notice is in bootstrap-grid.scss, bootstrap-reboot.scss, and bootstrap.scss, but none of those files are imported when picking just the parts that are needed. If the copyright notice was added to the _functions.scss file (which is required for all Sass compilations), then the copyright notice would be in all compilations of Bootstrap Sass.\r\n\r\nIt would be a little easier to have the notice there automatically rather than having to remember to add it manually to the Custom.scss file for each new project.",
